ActParliament of Canada Act
SubjectTravel - Red Tape Reduction Commission ** Five M.P.s **
PrecisOrder AUTHORIZING TRAVEL within Canada by the following members of the House of Commons, in their capacity as members of the RED TAPE REDUCTION COMMISSION, during the term of the Commission, subject to air travel conditions equivalent to those set out under National Joint Council or Treasury Board policies with any exceptions as may be approved by the Treasury Board: 1. Dean Allison, Member of Parliament for the constituency of Niagara West-Glanbrook 2. The Honourable Maxime Bernier, Member of Parliament for the constituency of Beauce 3. Lois Brown, Member of Parliament for the constituency of Newmarket-Aurora 4. Cathy McLeod, Member of Parliament for the constituency of Kamloops-Thompson-Cariboo 5. Chris Warkentin, Member of Parliament for the constituency of Peace River

subject: Travel - Red Tape Reduction Commission  ** Five M.P.s **
precis:
Order AUTHORIZING TRAVEL within Canada by the following members of the House of Commons, in their capacity as members of the RED TAPE REDUCTION COMMISSION, during the term of the Commission, subject to air travel conditions equivalent to those set out under National Joint Council or Treasury Board policies with any exceptions as may be approved by the Treasury Board:
1. Dean Allison, Member of Parliament for the constituency of Niagara West-Glanbrook
2.  The Honourable Maxime Bernier, Member of Parliament for the constituency of Beauce
3.  Lois Brown, Member of Parliament for the constituency of Newmarket-Aurora
4.  Cathy McLeod, Member of Parliament for the constituency of Kamloops-Thompson-Cariboo
5.  Chris Warkentin, Member of Parliament for the constituency of Peace River
